commit.message: Fixed a bug where the app asked for a Language's name to save even when there was not enough data to save.
Added the ability to save dropoff/cutoff settings into a Language and the DB.

Added dropoff/cutoff probability settings.
Fixed some bugs this brought into the scene.
Fixed a bug in the Weaver that sometimes just got rid of a substring to rewrite but didn't insert back the rewritten version.
Fixed a bug in the adapter that showed the language list as unsorted when cold starting it.
Added the capability of saving modificationsto current existing languages when loaded into the word generator, and added the capability of saving new configurations as new languages.

Fixed syllable concatenation funking up the rewrite rule application order.
Changed UI a bit.
You can now load a language, although you still can't save one.
Finally, the generation system is minimally visible. I can sleep now
